entry.def: The north-west is the direction which is halfway between north and west.

example.ex: ...Ushant, five miles out to the north-west.
example.tran: 西北方向5英里外的阿申特岛

entry.def: The north-west of a place, country, or region is the part which is towards the north-west.

example.ex: Labour took its pre-election campaign to the North-West.
example.tran: 工党在西北部地区展开了其选举前的竞选活动。

entry.def: If you go north-west, you travel towards the north-west.

example.ex: Take the narrow lane going north-west parallel with the railway line.
example.tran: 走和铁路线平行的那条西北向的窄巷。

entry.def: Something that is north-west of a place is positioned to the north-west of it.

example.ex: This was situated to the north-west of the town, a short walk from the railway station.
example.tran: 这里地处镇子的西北方，离火车站仅有一小段步行距离。

entry.def: The north-west part of a place, country, or region is the part which is towards the north-west.

example.ex: ...the north-west coast of the United States.

entry.tran: (风)从西北方吹来的;西北风的
entry.def: A north-west wind is a wind that blows from the north-west.

example.ex: A brisk north-west wind swept across the region.
example.tran: 寒冷干燥的西北风横扫了这个地区。
